scenario_text: Reduce the number of available vehicles from 2 to 1 to test the feasibility and impact on total distance traveled when vehicle capacity is constrained.
Increase the demand at each customer location by 50% to test the impact on total distance traveled and assess the feasibility under increased load conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD DATA": "demand = {i: int(d * 1.50) for i, d in demand.items()}"}

scenario_text: Scenario: 'Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to visit at least three customer locations to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues.'
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "for v in range(K): model += lpSum(x[i][j] for i in customers for j in customers if i != j) >= 3, f'MinCustomers_Vehicle_{v}'"}

scenario_text: Reduce the vehicle capacity from 50 to 30 to test the impact on total distance traveled and assess the feasibility when vehicles have significantly lower capacity.

Introduce a constraint that limits the maximum distance a single vehicle can travel to 150 units, to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues under restricted travel conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(distance[i][j] * x[i][j] for i in nodes for j in nodes) <= 150, 'MaxDistancePerVehicle'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to visit a specific high-demand customer location (e.g., customer 4 with demand 9) to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues under customer-specific assignment conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[i][4] for i in nodes) >= 1, 'Visit_Customer_4'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires one vehicle to serve all customers with demand greater than 5, to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues under high-demand customer grouping conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[i][j] for i in customers if demand[i] > 5 for j in nodes if j != i) >= 1, 'ServeHighDemandCustomers'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to visit at least one customer location that is more than 70 distance units away from the depot, to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues under long-distance travel conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[depot][j] for j in customers if distance[depot][j] > 70) >= 1, 'MinLongDistanceVisit'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to serve at least one customer located at the maximum distance from the depot, to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues under extreme travel conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[depot][j] for j in customers if distance[depot][j] == max(distance[depot][k] for k in customers)) >= 1, 'MinServe_MaxDist'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to visit exactly two customer locations with the highest demands (e.g., customers 4 and 11 with demands 9), to assess the impact on route optimization and potential feasibility issues under high-demand customer balancing conditions.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[i][j] for i in customers for j in customers if demand[i] >= 9) == 2, 'Visit_TopDemands'"}
